messages.messageBody:
Wow those photos from the Aizu Festival were so cool! I have never been able to go to one of the many festivals of Japan or any country and to be ablt to see photos from a festival with the Shinsengumi (albeit only characters) is truly wonderful. Thank you for taking these photos and sharing them with us all.
----- Original Message -----
From: Jon Mesina
To: SHQ@yahoogroups.com
Sent: Tuesday, October 05, 2004 10:17 AM
Subject: Re: [SHQ] Re: Aizu festival photos


Excellent pics! Thank you Tama for taking them and to Barb for putting them up!


~Okita

----- Original Message -----
From: GBattista (hajimenokizu)
To: SHQ@yahoogroups.com
Sent: Sunday, October 03, 2004 5:36 PM
Subject: [SHQ] Re: Aizu festival photos



--- In SHQ@yahoogroups.com, BarbaraSheridan <bsher213@b...> wrote:
> I have many many many photos up courtesy of Tama our #1 fangirl in
the
> field-- http://www.shinsengumihq.com/aizu_festival_report.htm
>
> the pictures open in their own windows so you can just x them off
then
> click to the next one I didn't feel like giving them their own
pages
> with back and next buttons --maybe another day...
>
> And Tama, it seems I don' t have # 133 can you send it?
>
> --
> Barbara Sheridan
> http://www.barbarasheridan.net
>
>
>

Thank you Barb and Tama for the pics... Those pictures of Hijikata
and Shimada Kai was VERY welcome ^_^
I was a bit thrown though on the picture of Saitou-sama, I don't know
he seemed a bit off.
